items.title: US permits Boeing to resume certifications on some planes
items.description: The FAA announcement marks a sign of progress in Boeing's turnaround following deadly MAX crashes in 2018 and 2019.

items.title: ByteDance to get about 50% of TikTok US profit under Trump deal
items.description: The profit-sharing arrangement is the latest twist in an extraordinary corporate drama that has played out across multiple US administrations

items.title: Tata Motors makes major leadership rejig, appoints Shailesh Chandra as MD & CEO
items.description: Tata Motors News: The company’s Group Chief Financial Officer (CFO) PB Balaji has resigned and will step down on November 17. PB Balaji will take charge as the CEO of JLR Automotive in the UK, effective the same day.

items.title: HUL says around 40% of company's portfolio benefits from GST revision
items.description: HUL News: Will ensure GST benefits are passed to customers via competitive prices; GST reforms expected to drive long-term demand across key categories, says HUL

items.title: India proposes relaxing fuel efficiency norms for small cars boosting Suzuki shares
items.description: Fuel efficiency rules are designed to incentivise higher sales of low-emission car models, mainly electric, if companies want to avoid paying penalties for non-compliance.
